<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 02 at 11:38PM CDT until May 03 at 4:00AM CDT by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1145 PM CDT
FOR LOGAN...SCOTT...NORTHERN POLK...SOUTHWESTERN YELL AND
NORTHWESTERN MONTGOMERY COUNTIES...
At 1138 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 6 miles southwest of Booneville to near Cardiff to 11
miles northeast of Mena, moving east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Booneville...                     Waldron...
Paris...                          Mansfield...
Magazine...                       Subiaco...
Oden...                           Ratcliff...
Blue Mountain...                  Beauchamp...
Cardiff...                        Muddy Creek WMA...
Stonehouse Recreation Area...     Gravelly...
Mount Magazine...                 Echo...
Oliver...                         Queen Wilhelmina State Park...
Caulksville...                    Acorn...
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for western and
central Arkansas.
For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
